name: Giulio Setti
comments: Choral conductor born in Treviglio. He served as chorus master of opera houses in Italy, Cairo, Cologne and Buenos Aires prior to coming to the US in 1908; there he was engaged as chorus master of the Metropolitan Opera in New York. He remained in the post twenty-seven years before retiring after which he returned to Italy.

Especially in the 19th century La Fenice became the site of many famous operatic premieres at which the works of several of the four major bel canto era composers – Gioachino Rossini , Vincenzo Bellini , Gaetano Donizetti & Giuseppe Verdi – were performed.

name: Giuditta Pasta
personal_name: Giuditta Angiola Maria Costanza Pasta née Negri
comments: Soprano opera singer, who sang regularly in London, Paris, Milan and Naples between 1824 and 1837. In Milan she created three roles which were written for her voice. They were the title role in Gaetano Donizetti 's "Anna Bolena" in 1830 (and which was that composer's greatest success to date), Amina in Vincenzo Bellini 's "La sonnambula" and the protagonist's part of his Norma (both in 1831), which became three of her major successes.

name: Orchestra del Teatro alla Scala
comments: "La Scala" is an opera house in Milan. Most of Italy's greatest operatic artists, and many of the finest singers from around the world, have appeared at La Scala. The theatre is regarded as one of the leading opera and ballet theatres in the world and is home to the Coro del Teatro Alla Sca, la La Scala Theatre Ballet and the Orchestra del Teatro alla Scala.

name: Tullio Serafin

He had an unparalleled reputation as a coach of young opera singers and famously harnessed and developed Maria Callas's considerable talents.

name: Rosa Ponselle
